  "texts": [
    "It divides the input data into several groups where the system is not aware of the groups beforehand.",
    "Surprisingly, it has become popular in fruit maturity because of its well-known applications like feature extraction and pattern recognition.",
    "For example, Tu et al. (2018) apply k-means clustering to classify the maturity stages of passion fruits and achieve 91.52% of accuracy.",
    "Moradi et al. (2012) consider fuzzy c-means to classify pomegranates based on their maturity level through magnetic resonance (MR) images and able to reach an accuracy of 85.93%.",
    "Gong et al. (Gong et al., 2014) use hierarchical clustering to classify apples into 5 groups based on their maturity level."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, Tu et al. (2018) apply k-means clustering to classify the maturity stages of passion fruits and achieve 91.52% of accuracy.",
    "Moradi et al. (2012) consider fuzzy c-means to classify pomegranates based on their maturity level through magnetic resonance (MR) images and able to reach an accuracy of 85.93%.",
    "Gong et al. (Gong et al., 2014) use hierarchical clustering to classify apples into 5 groups based on their maturity level."
